  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "A large watercolor drawing (510 x 680 mm) by **George Hendrik Breitner** (Rotterdam, 1857 – Amsterdam, 1923), depicting the professional model **Adolphe (Louis Edouard) Boutard** (Tebing Tinggi, Sumatra, 1839 – The Hague, 1885) in Orientalist costume. Made c. 1883 in The Hague — likely during a session at Pulchri Studio where Breitner made multiple studies of Boutard under different Orientalist titles (\"The Arab,\" \"The Negro,\" \"Seated African\"). Acquired by Teylers in 2020. Designated one of Teylers' **50 Topstukken**.",
